// P10.5 / Audit-B — Debug build configuration overlay.
//
// In DEBUG builds `AdsConfig` always returns Google's official test
// unit ids (see `Services/AdsConfig.swift`) regardless of what's in
// `Info.plist`, so most `ADUNIT_ID_*` keys remain unset here. The
// few keys defined below are required because they are read at SDK
// initialisation time (not via `AdsConfig.resolve`) or by non-ad
// code paths that don't have a DEBUG short-circuit:
//
//   * `GAD_APPLICATION_ID` — `GADMobileAds.sharedInstance().start(...)`
//     uses the Info.plist value verbatim. Without this the SDK fails
//     to initialise and emits a warning at every app launch.
//     Audit-B: variabilised so Release.xcconfig can override with a
//     real production app id.
//   * `ADUNIT_ID_REWARDED_INTERSTITIAL` — kept here as a placeholder
//     to mirror `Release.xcconfig` and to give the Info.plist key
//     `AdUnitID_RewardedInterstitial` a non-empty resolution at build
//     time. The runtime `AdsConfig.rewardedInterstitial` still routes
//     through the DEBUG test-id short-circuit.
//   * `COUPON_PUBLIC_KEY` — left empty in DEBUG so `CouponVerifier`
//     falls back to its 32-byte zero placeholder. Production builds
//     replace via `Release.xcconfig`.
//
// Audit-B: previously this file was effectively empty; the missing
// `GAD_APPLICATION_ID` definition meant DEBUG builds would have
// resolved Info.plist's `$(GAD_APPLICATION_ID)` to the literal
// substitution sentinel and the SDK would have failed to start.
//
// Note: Adding this file to the Debug build configurations also
// confirms the xcconfig wiring is correct end-to-end (build settings
// resolve from xcconfig → target → project for both Debug and
// Release).

GAD_APPLICATION_ID = ca-app-pub-3940256099942544~1458002511
ADUNIT_ID_REWARDED_INTERSTITIAL = ca-app-pub-3940256099942544/6978759866
COUPON_PUBLIC_KEY =

SWIFT_TREAT_WARNINGS_AS_ERRORS = YES
